               <head>Commentary on book 5 of Rumi’s Masnavi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī by Muḥammad ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Quṭb al-Dīn</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010113603 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1043C-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled commentary on daftar 5 of the 
                <title key="work_20506">Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title>of 
                <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī</persName> (d. 670/1271) by 
                <persName key="person_f7329" role="aut">Mawlānā Muḥammad ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Quṭb al-Dīn</persName>, composed circa 1700.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 135v): completed by 
                <persName key="person_f8099" role="scr">Gangā Rām Kāyath</persName>, resident of 
                <placeName>Nāytvārah</placeName>(?), 8 Muḥarram… (year not entered). Datable to early nineteenth century.
                        </p>
                        <p>Rough nastaʿlīq.</p>
                        <p>Occasional annotations and corrections in margins.</p>
                        <p>Intermittent pencil foliation.</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding.</p>
                        <p>Binding with delaminating detached board (end) with combed marbled paper, reddish brown leather edges; spine damaged.</p>
                        <p>Folios mostly bound; water stains; folio 1 torn.</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7328">Muḥammad ʿAbd al-ʿAlī ibn Quṭb al-Dīn</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f7328">محمّد عبد العلى ابن قطب الدّين</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
